      "timestamp": "2025-11-19T18:51:17.903152Z",
      "entry_type": "status_change",
      "title": "Task Completed: Analyze BMAD index-template.md and define exact index.md structure",
      "author": "claude-code",
      "content": "Analyzed BMAD document access mechanism and defined the 7-section index.md structure based on analysis/bmad-document-access-mechanism.md. \n\n**Defined Structure:**\n\n1. **Project Header** (Lines ~1-10, ~200-300 tokens)\n   - Project name with markdown h1\n   - Primary languages (comma-separated list)\n   - Framework/tech stack summary\n   - Generation timestamp\n   \n2. **Project Overview** (Lines ~12-25, ~800-1200 tokens)\n   - 2-3 paragraph high-level description\n   - Project purpose and domain\n   - Key business capabilities\n   - Target token size: 800-1200 tokens\n\n3. **Quick Reference** (Lines ~27-50, ~600-900 tokens)\n   - File/class/function counts\n   - Entry points (main files, startup scripts)\n   - Tech stack (languages, frameworks, databases)\n   - Architecture patterns (MVC, microservices, etc.)\n   - Database info\n   - Deployment platform\n   - Target token size: 600-900 tokens\n\n4. **Documentation Files** (Lines ~52-80, ~800-1500 tokens depending on shard count)\n   - Links to generated shards with descriptions\n   - Core shards: project-overview.md, architecture.md, source-tree-analysis.md, component-inventory.md, development-guide.md\n   - Conditional shards: api-contracts.md, data-models.md, deep-dive-{area}.md\n   - Each link includes: filename, purpose, when to reference\n   - Target token size: 100-200 tokens per shard description\n\n5. **For AI-Assisted Development** (Lines ~82-110, ~800-1200 tokens)\n   - Usage guidance by feature type\n   - UI-only features -> Reference: architecture.md, component-inventory.md\n   - API/Backend features -> Reference: architecture.md, api-contracts.md, data-models.md\n   - Full-stack features -> Reference: All architecture docs\n   - Deployment changes -> Reference: development-guide.md, architecture.md\n   - Target token size: 800-1200 tokens\n\n6. **Machine-Readable Documentation** (Lines ~112-120, ~200-300 tokens)\n   - Link to JSON format documentation\n   - Brief description of JSON structure\n   - When to use JSON vs markdown\n   - Target token size: 200-300 tokens\n\n7. **Optional: Project Structure** (Lines ~122-160, ~500-800 tokens for multi-part projects)\n   - Only included for multi-part projects (client/server monorepos)\n   - Lists each part with: name, type, location, tech stack\n   - Part-specific documentation links (architecture-client.md, architecture-server.md)\n   - Integration architecture reference\n   - Target token size: 500-800 tokens when present\n\n**Template Variables Defined:**\n- {{project_name}} - Project display name\n- {{primary_languages}} - Comma-separated language list\n- {{frameworks}} - Main frameworks/libraries\n- {{timestamp}} - ISO format generation timestamp\n- {{file_count}} - Total files analyzed\n- {{class_count}} - Total classes/components found\n- {{function_count}} - Total functions/methods found\n- {{entry_points}} - Main entry files\n- {{tech_stack}} - Complete tech stack summary\n- {{architecture_patterns}} - Architecture pattern list\n- {{database_info}} - Database type and key info\n- {{deployment_platform}} - Where app is deployed\n- {{shard_links}} - Generated list of shard file links with descriptions\n- {{has_api_contracts}} - Boolean for api-contracts.md inclusion\n- {{has_data_models}} - Boolean for data-models.md inclusion\n- {{deep_dive_areas}} - List of deep-dive topics if any exist\n- {{is_multipart}} - Boolean for multi-part project detection\n- {{parts}} - Array of part objects (name, type, location, tech_stack) if multipart\n\n**Overall Target Token Size:** 3,000-7,000 tokens total\n\nThe structure is optimized as an **intelligent AI entry point** for INDEX_GUIDED loading strategy, enabling context-aware documentation loading while preventing context exhaustion.\n\nFiles analyzed: analysis/bmad-document-access-mechanism.md (519 lines). No tests required for research task.",
